@startuml sequence_diagnostics_failure
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Diagnostics on Failure - Partial Report

actor User
participant "CreateCodeGeneratorCommand" as CMD
participant "GenerationTimer" as GT
participant "ICommandService" as CS
participant "DiagnosticsCollector" as DC
participant "DiagnosticsRenderer" as DR

User -> CMD: HandleAsync(name, ..., diagnostics=true)
CMD -> GT: new GenerationTimer()

CMD -> GT: TimeStep("Validate options")
CMD -> CMD: scope.Dispose() [12ms]

CMD -> GT: TimeStep("Create directories")
CMD -> CMD: scope.Dispose() [3ms]

CMD -> GT: TimeStep("Create solution file")
CMD -> CS: Start("dotnet new sln")
CMD -> CMD: scope.Dispose() [847ms]

CMD -> GT: TimeStep("Add project to solution")
CMD -> CS: Start("dotnet sln add")
CS --> CMD: CliProcessException!
CMD -> CMD: scope.Dispose() [15ms]

CMD -> CMD: catch (Exception)

CMD -> DC: CollectEnvironment("1.2.0")
DC --> CMD: EnvironmentInfo

CMD -> CMD: Build partial DiagnosticsReport\n(4 steps, last one failed)

CMD -> DR: Render(report)
DR --> User: Partial timing table\nshowing completed steps

CMD --> User: "Error: dotnet sln add failed\n(exit code 1)"

note right of DR: Report shows which\nstep failed and total\ntime before failure.

@enduml
